# Filament v2 — the keys: electric PIANO, not electric string.
# What made livewire stringy: detuned saw pad + PWM churn + vibrato +
# sustained envelope. All gone. This is the Wurlitzer recipe: a sine
# reed with a narrow-pulse edge, KEYED envelope (fast attack, real
# decay, low sustain), and the electricity comes from drive 2.2 — hard
# velocities bark, soft ones stay round, which the per-voice shaper
# does dynamically. No pitch LFO, no width churn. Keys, with current.
waveform 0
osc2_wave 1
osc2_pitch 0
osc2_level 0.25
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 12
osc3_level 0.1
detune 2
sub 0.1
circuit 0
key_track 0.7
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0
pulse_width 0.3
attack 0.003
decay 1.1
sustain 0.25
release 0.3
filter_env 1.1
filter_attack 0.001
filter_decay 0.25
filter_sustain 0.3
filter_release 0.3
cutoff 1000
resonance 0.7
drive 2.2
saturation 1.1
hpf 60
volume 0.5
octave 4
noise 0
fuzz 0
spring 0.12
lfo_rate 0.5
lfo_shape 0.5
lfo_pitch 0
lfo_filter 0
lfo_pwm 0
